### 2. State and Accounting Correctness (Trading-Specific)

**Identify the system's single source of truth for each piece of state.**

| State | Source of Truth | Replicas/Views | Reconciliation Strategy | Risk |
|-------|------------------|----------------|--------------------------|------|
| Position open/closed | | | | |
| Entry price | | | | |
| Quantity/side | | | | |
| Cash balance | | | | |
| Portfolio NAV | | | | |

**Accounting invariants (must be true):**
- [ ] Entry/exit prices are persisted and used for P&L calculation
- [ ] Commission and slippage are applied consistently (entry vs exit)
- [ ] P&L uses correct sign conventions for long/short
- [ ] Position lifecycle is consistent across modules (no split-brain)

---

### 3. Traceability and Auditability (Non-Negotiable)

**Verify end-to-end decision trace propagation.**

| Decision Point | decision_id generated? | Propagated to logs? | Propagated to trades/events? | Notes |
|----------------|------------------------|----------------------|------------------------------|------|
| Signal generation | | | | |
| Risk checks | | | | |
| Order/Fill simulation | | | | |
| Position open/close | | | | |

- [ ] Every trade has a `decision_id` (or explicit rationale why not)
- [ ] Logs contain enough fields to reconstruct the decision chain
- [ ] No "silent" state transitions without an audit event

---

### 4. Failure Mode and Recovery Review

**Validate that failures are safe, loud, and recoverable.**

| Failure Mode | Expected Behavior | Implemented? | Test Exists? |
|--------------|-------------------|--------------|--------------|
| Missing/NaN data | Raise/skip with explicit log | | |
| Strategy exception | Fail fast + decision_id | | |
| Risk module exception | Fail closed (no trade) | | |
| Partial state update | Prevent or reconcile | | |

**Recovery questions:**
- [ ] Can state be reconstructed from the journal/logs alone?
- [ ] Is the system idempotent on replay (same inputs -> same outputs)?
- [ ] Are there reconciliation hooks between state stores?

